                    <xpath>/Defs/ThingDef[defName="OGI_Gun_LasGun_Catachan"]/label</xpath>
                    <value>
                        <label>lasgun (Catachan pattern carbine)</label>
                    </value>
                </li>

                <li Class="PatchOperationReplace">
                    <xpath>/Defs/ThingDef[defName="OGI_Gun_LasGun_Catachan"]/description</xpath>
                    <value>
                        <description>The Lascarbine is a carbine form of the standard Imperial Lasgun that is easier to carry and to aim that its larger counterpart. It will often possess a folding stock to further optimise its size. However, as a result of these modificatios, a Lascarbine has a shorter effective range and will fire fewer shots before depleting its power pack when compared to the standard Lasgun.\n\nThe Mark IV "Catachan" Lascarbine has less cowling that the M36 Pattern, and therefore is lighter and easier to carry. It also has a slightly reduced effective range offset against an increased rate of fire, hence it being favoured in dense jungle environs frequented by the Catachan regigments.</description>
                    </value>
                </li>

<!--  ==============================================================================================================  -->
<!--     + ALL CASES (cont)                                                                                           -->
